<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1395,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1395,1421]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Projections of gonocoxite rounded apically, with regular rows of microtrichia in grooves (
<figureCitation box="[1348,1420,1396,1422]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,255,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,194,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,194,1733]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Paratrizygia alvesi, sp. nov. Male terminalia, ventral view. Holotype. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/198302/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
Fig. 
<number box="[1404,1420,1396,1422]" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonostyle hook-shaped, with a rounded inner projection before apex, four dark spines apically. Aedeagus without a medial projection directed ventrally at base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
